A '''virtually safe dose''' (VSD) may be determined for those [[carcinogen]]s not assumed to have a threshold. Virtually safe doses are calculated by regulatory agencies to represent the level of exposure to such carcinogenic agents at which an excess of cancers greater than that level accepted by society is not expected.<ref>Derelanko, M.J. and Hollinger, M.A. (Eds). CRC Handbook of Toxicology. 1995. CRC Press. Boca Raton, FL.</ref>
